text.tspan: Estimated cumulative excess deaths during COVID-19 in the last 12
For countries that have not reported all-cause mortality data for a given week, an estimate is shown, with uncertainty
interval. If reported data is available, that value only is shown.
Data source: The Economist (2024); World Health Organization (2026)
Note: For some countries, all-cause deaths and COVID-19 deaths use different date schemes, in which one refers to when the death
occurred and the other to when it was reported. This difference could produce an artificial lag between the two time series.
